children.content: A young man has died after falling from a supermarket roof in the city of Rouen.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Emmanuel Macron has said a third of the protesters arrested on Thursday night local time were "young people, sometimes very young". “We sometimes have the feeling that some of them are living out, in the streets, the video games that have intoxicated them,” he said of rioters. France's interior minister said some of those arrested have been as young as 13, with the average age being 17.
